Binary Search Example (Java)

Array (must be sorted):

Index : 0   1   2   3   4
Array : 10  20  30  40  50
Key   : 40

Step 1
low = 0
high = 4

mid = (0 + 4) / 2 = 2

arr[mid] = 30

Since 40 > 30, search the right half.

low = mid + 1 = 3
high = 4


Step 2
mid = (3 + 4) / 2 = 3

arr[mid] = 40

Key found at index 3.

